WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:07.280 --> 00:00:09.720
FEMALE SPEAKER: Hi, everybody.

00:00:09.720 --> 00:00:12.080
So thank you so
much for being here.

00:00:12.080 --> 00:00:16.710
Today we are absolutely
delighted to welcome Chef Alain

00:00:16.710 --> 00:00:19.380
Ducasse, one of the
most renowned chefs

00:00:19.380 --> 00:00:20.920
of his generation.

00:00:20.920 --> 00:00:24.480
And he's here to talk to us
about his book "J'aime London,"

00:00:24.480 --> 00:00:27.670
which he's recently launched.

00:00:27.670 --> 00:00:33.180
Chef Ducasse is a
restaurant creator,

00:00:33.180 --> 00:00:37.130
a contemporary innkeeper, an
educator, and a publisher.

00:00:37.130 --> 00:00:39.470
And over the past
30 years, he has

00:00:39.470 --> 00:00:41.510
developed a unique
savoir-faire which

00:00:41.510 --> 00:00:45.230
has helped to shape the
contemporary art of living

00:00:45.230 --> 00:00:46.610
and eating.

00:00:46.610 --> 00:00:49.590
And he is joined by his
old friend and fellow

00:00:49.590 --> 00:00:53.880
chef, Michel Roux
Jr, who has kindly

00:00:53.880 --> 00:00:57.070
written the forward to
the book "J'aime London."

00:00:57.070 --> 00:00:59.440
And he will be conducting
the conversation.

00:00:59.440 --> 00:01:04.170
And he's also almost fresh from
the London Marathon on Sunday.

00:01:04.170 --> 00:01:08.550
So if he hobbles onto the stage,
then you'll know why that is.

00:01:08.550 --> 00:01:12.856
So welcome to Chef
Ducasse and Chef Roux.

00:01:12.856 --> 00:01:16.328
[APPLAUSE]

00:01:25.752 --> 00:01:29.446
ALAIN DUCASSE: [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:01:29.446 --> 00:01:30.820
MICHEL ROUX JR:
Hello, everybody.

00:01:30.820 --> 00:01:33.590
Thankfully there were
no steps to climb up.

00:01:33.590 --> 00:01:37.930
A nice easy, easy up
onto the stage here,

00:01:37.930 --> 00:01:39.470
and a nice, comfy chair.

00:01:39.470 --> 00:01:40.360
Good.

00:01:40.360 --> 00:01:40.870
Thank you.

00:01:40.870 --> 00:01:43.050
Thank you for coming here today.

00:01:43.050 --> 00:01:45.970
Thank you for having us.

00:01:45.970 --> 00:01:52.140
My friend Alain and fellow chef,
god to a lot of young chefs,

00:01:52.140 --> 00:01:57.810
and someone that is
highly, highly respected.

00:01:57.810 --> 00:01:59.830
An all time great.

00:01:59.830 --> 00:02:01.080
An all time great.

00:02:01.080 --> 00:02:03.670
So we're going to get to know
a little bit more about Alain--

00:02:03.670 --> 00:02:05.220
about his philosophy.

00:02:05.220 --> 00:02:10.861
And although he
understands English,

00:02:10.861 --> 00:02:12.360
he says his English
isn't that good.

00:02:12.360 --> 00:02:14.445
But he can say a
few words, so we're

00:02:14.445 --> 00:02:16.820
going to try and coax a little
bit of English out of him.

00:02:16.820 --> 00:02:20.210
But I'm here to translate and
to ask him a few questions.

00:02:20.210 --> 00:02:24.462
ALAIN DUCASSE: [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:02:24.462 --> 00:02:25.420
MICHEL ROUX JR: I will.

00:02:25.420 --> 00:02:26.020
I will do my best.

00:02:26.020 --> 00:02:27.353
ALAIN DUCASSE: [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:02:27.353 --> 00:02:28.850
MICHEL ROUX JR: I
will do my best.

00:02:28.850 --> 00:02:31.500
So Alain, first of all,
I want to find out--

00:02:31.500 --> 00:02:33.560
or we would like to
find out-- a little bit

00:02:33.560 --> 00:02:38.380
about you, how you started.

00:02:38.380 --> 00:02:39.800
It's well documented about me.

00:02:39.800 --> 00:02:41.367
I was nearly born in a kitchen.

00:02:41.367 --> 00:02:43.200
But I would like to
know, and everybody here

00:02:43.200 --> 00:02:45.380
would like to know,
how you started.

00:02:45.380 --> 00:02:48.430
How Alain Ducasse, a little
boy, got into cooking.

00:02:48.430 --> 00:02:51.820
[SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:02:51.820 --> 00:03:04.000
ALAIN DUCASSE: [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:03:04.000 --> 00:03:07.150
MICHEL ROUX JR: So Alain said,
like a lot of French kids,

00:03:07.150 --> 00:03:10.480
their grandmother
was cooking at home.

00:03:10.480 --> 00:03:11.307
Grandma's cooking.

00:03:11.307 --> 00:03:12.640
I remember my grandma's cooking.

00:03:12.640 --> 00:03:14.010
It was beautiful.

00:03:14.010 --> 00:03:15.000
Beautiful.

00:03:15.000 --> 00:03:16.510
And that is what inspired him.

00:03:16.510 --> 00:03:18.580
He was born on a farm in
the southwest of France.

00:03:18.580 --> 00:03:19.330
He has the accent.

00:03:19.330 --> 00:03:22.414
I don't know if you clocked
that one, the accent

00:03:22.414 --> 00:03:24.080
of the southwest of
France, probably one

00:03:24.080 --> 00:03:26.060
of the most beautiful
regions in France.

00:03:26.060 --> 00:03:26.880
Very rich.

00:03:26.880 --> 00:03:28.350
[FRENCH]

00:03:28.350 --> 00:03:48.210
ALAIN DUCASSE: [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:03:48.210 --> 00:03:53.920
MICHEL ROUX JR: A real idyllic
childhood in a village.

00:03:53.920 --> 00:04:01.120
Being able to go to your local
farm or shop to buy the goods.

00:04:01.120 --> 00:04:04.940
[FRENCH] as we call it
in France-- real land.

00:04:04.940 --> 00:04:06.800
And the beauty of
that part of France

00:04:06.800 --> 00:04:11.250
is that it has great
sunshine, but it also

00:04:11.250 --> 00:04:13.560
has the sea air, as well.

00:04:13.560 --> 00:04:17.339
So it has proper seasons
and it's very rich and lush.

00:04:17.339 --> 00:04:21.410
And the ingredients that
come there are beautiful.

00:04:21.410 --> 00:04:56.930
ALAIN DUCASSE: [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:04:56.930 --> 00:04:58.620
MICHEL ROUX JR: I
think that's where

00:04:58.620 --> 00:04:59.840
his inspiration comes from.

00:04:59.840 --> 00:05:02.790
And it is from
those early years,

00:05:02.790 --> 00:05:05.940
and being able to pick
up wonderful ingredients,

00:05:05.940 --> 00:05:10.070
and then being inspired by them
to create beautiful dishes.

00:05:10.070 --> 00:05:13.330
But dishes that have a
meaning, that have an origin.

00:05:13.330 --> 00:05:14.027
[FRENCH]

00:05:14.027 --> 00:05:15.360
ALAIN DUCASSE: [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:05:15.360 --> 00:05:16.735
MICHEL ROUX JR:
[SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:05:16.735 --> 00:05:22.960
ALAIN DUCASSE: [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:05:22.960 --> 00:05:24.630
MICHEL ROUX JR: So he's keen.

00:05:24.630 --> 00:05:26.230
He said he wasn't
learning enough so

00:05:26.230 --> 00:05:29.730
he escaped the village
and went to a hotel

00:05:29.730 --> 00:05:31.855
catering school, of which
there are many in France.

00:05:31.855 --> 00:05:32.550
ALAIN DUCASSE: [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:05:32.550 --> 00:05:33.716
MICHEL ROUX JR: In Bordeaux.

00:05:33.716 --> 00:05:35.110
ALAIN DUCASSE: [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:05:35.110 --> 00:05:36.484
MICHEL ROUX JR:
[SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:05:36.484 --> 00:05:43.292
ALAIN DUCASSE: [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:05:43.292 --> 00:05:44.750
MICHEL ROUX JR:
He's just mentioned

00:05:44.750 --> 00:05:49.709
some of the greats of France
in passing, in passing.

00:05:49.709 --> 00:05:51.250
Michel Guerard in
the southwest-- one

00:05:51.250 --> 00:05:52.950
of the most beautiful places.

00:05:52.950 --> 00:05:55.260
If you haven't been to
Michel Guerard before,

00:05:55.260 --> 00:05:58.810
go and spend a week there.

00:05:58.810 --> 00:06:01.570
Eugenie-les-Bains--
it is outstanding.

00:06:01.570 --> 00:06:04.830
I remember my best
ever dessert-- sorry,

00:06:04.830 --> 00:06:07.980
but I'm going-- my
best ever dessert,

00:06:07.980 --> 00:06:11.820
and it has yet to be
topped, was quite simply

00:06:11.820 --> 00:06:14.120
a wild strawberry tart.

00:06:14.120 --> 00:06:16.400
That sounds just
banal, doesn't it?

00:06:16.400 --> 00:06:17.510
[FRENCH]

00:06:17.510 --> 00:06:19.957
ALAIN DUCASSE: [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:06:19.957 --> 00:06:22.620
MICHEL ROUX JR: It
was extraordinary.

00:06:22.620 --> 00:06:24.570
So sorry.

00:06:24.570 --> 00:06:27.370
Eugenie-les-Bains--
worked there.

00:06:27.370 --> 00:06:30.420
And then you worked
for Alain Chapel.

00:06:30.420 --> 00:06:32.410
I just missed Alain.

00:06:32.410 --> 00:06:35.340
I think Alain finished in
August and I started work

00:06:35.340 --> 00:06:36.050
in September.

00:06:36.050 --> 00:06:37.680
ALAIN DUCASSE: [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:06:37.680 --> 00:06:39.950
MICHEL ROUX JR: He's a
year or two older than me.

00:06:39.950 --> 00:06:41.730
We worked in the
same place for Alain

00:06:41.730 --> 00:06:44.972
Chapel-- an extraordinary chef.

00:06:44.972 --> 00:06:45.930
What did Alain Chapel--

00:06:45.930 --> 00:06:50.535
ALAIN DUCASSE: [SPEAKING FRENCH]
was a perfect experience.

00:06:53.440 --> 00:07:08.500
[SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:07:08.500 --> 00:07:11.030
MICHEL ROUX JR: The
experience at Alain Chapel

00:07:11.030 --> 00:07:12.520
taught him rigor.

00:07:12.520 --> 00:07:15.500
But also the fact that
Alain Chapel was way ahead

00:07:15.500 --> 00:07:21.490
of his years, and he was a
modern chef of that era-- quite

00:07:21.490 --> 00:07:22.320
extraordinary.

00:07:22.320 --> 00:07:25.350
I learned well, I always
go back to Alain Chapel.

00:07:25.350 --> 00:07:27.005
For me he was my
strongest influence.

00:07:27.005 --> 00:07:27.390
ALAIN DUCASSE:
Yeah, for me, too.

00:07:27.390 --> 00:07:29.710
MICHEL ROUX JR: And I
think Alain, as well.

00:07:29.710 --> 00:07:30.260
A great man.

00:07:30.260 --> 00:07:53.690
ALAIN DUCASSE: [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:07:53.690 --> 00:07:55.690
MICHEL ROUX JR: Alain
Chapel was haute cuisine--

00:07:55.690 --> 00:07:59.520
the true meaning of it-- in
the same way as haute couture

00:07:59.520 --> 00:08:03.710
is now, and will always exist,
and should always exist.

00:08:03.710 --> 00:08:08.630
So he really was the
benchmark, Alain Chapel.

00:08:08.630 --> 00:08:12.300
Sadly no longer open, and
sadly no longer with us.

00:08:12.300 --> 00:08:16.130
[FRENCH] Monaco?

00:08:16.130 --> 00:08:55.209
ALAIN DUCASSE: [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:08:55.209 --> 00:08:56.750
MICHEL ROUX JR: It
was a huge gamble.

00:08:56.750 --> 00:09:00.830
The Prince Rainier, in Monaco,
got Alain as a young chef

00:09:00.830 --> 00:09:03.090
and said, look,
this is what I want.

00:09:03.090 --> 00:09:07.280
I want three Michelin Stars and
you've got four years to do it,

00:09:07.280 --> 00:09:09.980
and threw down the gauntlet.

00:09:09.980 --> 00:09:13.420
And Alain achieved the
three stars in 33 months.

00:09:13.420 --> 00:09:16.570
So he certainly
did achieve that.

00:09:16.570 --> 00:09:17.980
And it's still going strong.

00:09:17.980 --> 00:09:21.060
I was very fortunate
and honored to be there

00:09:21.060 --> 00:09:26.060
for the birthday celebrations
two years ago, now, wasn't it?

00:09:26.060 --> 00:09:28.750
It goes so quickly.

00:09:28.750 --> 00:09:29.800
Truly extraordinary.

00:09:29.800 --> 00:09:33.326
And it is, again, I
urge you-- this is

00:09:33.326 --> 00:09:34.700
one place where
you've got to go.

00:09:34.700 --> 00:09:36.730
It's got to be on
your bucket list.

00:09:36.730 --> 00:09:40.380
Go to Monaco, and go to Alain's
restaurant there, Le Louis XV.

00:09:40.380 --> 00:09:43.890
It is extraordinary,
extraordinary.

00:09:43.890 --> 00:09:47.800
And [INAUDIBLE] its
longevity, its consistency--

00:09:47.800 --> 00:09:50.500
that is the hallmark
of a great man

00:09:50.500 --> 00:09:52.620
and the hallmark of
a great restaurant,

00:09:52.620 --> 00:09:55.640
is that it is consistent--
consistently good,

00:09:55.640 --> 00:09:59.482
delivering the goods
time and time again.

00:09:59.482 --> 00:10:00.190
Monaco, [FRENCH].

00:10:03.447 --> 00:10:04.280
[INTERPOSING VOICES]

00:10:11.940 --> 00:10:53.006
ALAIN DUCASSE: [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:10:53.006 --> 00:10:54.420
MICHEL ROUX JR:
So his philosophy

00:10:54.420 --> 00:10:58.320
behind that cuisine--
Riviera Cuisine-- was

00:10:58.320 --> 00:11:04.870
to take humble goods and very
classic, instantly recognizable

00:11:04.870 --> 00:11:08.590
dishes-- such as bouillabaisse,
an aioli, or the dishes

00:11:08.590 --> 00:11:12.230
that you would recognize on a
menu in the south of France,

00:11:12.230 --> 00:11:16.680
in that area-- and to make
that into haute gastronomy--

00:11:16.680 --> 00:11:20.580
something that is worthy
of three Michelin Stars.

00:11:20.580 --> 00:11:23.810
So using the great produce--
of which there are so many,

00:11:23.810 --> 00:11:27.620
but you have to find
them-- and making them

00:11:27.620 --> 00:11:31.400
into exquisite food,
exquisite dishes,

00:11:31.400 --> 00:11:35.730
but still with that
philosophy of Riviera Cuisine.

00:11:38.370 --> 00:12:04.570
ALAIN DUCASSE: [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:12:04.570 --> 00:12:06.770
MICHEL ROUX JR:
[SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:12:06.770 --> 00:12:13.351
ALAIN DUCASSE: [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:12:13.351 --> 00:12:17.000
MICHEL ROUX JR:
[SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:12:17.000 --> 00:12:19.044
ALAIN DUCASSE: [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:12:19.044 --> 00:12:21.210
MICHEL ROUX JR: The politics
of the Michelin guide--

00:12:21.210 --> 00:12:22.959
I don't think we're
going to go into that.

00:12:22.959 --> 00:12:26.480
But Alain was explaining
that he got a phone call

00:12:26.480 --> 00:12:31.517
from Joel Robuchon,
another amazing chef,

00:12:31.517 --> 00:12:33.850
to announce that he was
retiring and that if Alain would

00:12:33.850 --> 00:12:36.320
be interested in taking his
place in a restaurant in Paris.

00:12:36.320 --> 00:12:38.360
And then he said, well,
just over the phone,

00:12:38.360 --> 00:12:39.870
he couldn't believe that
Robuchon was phoning.

00:12:39.870 --> 00:12:41.078
He said, well, yeah, why not.

00:12:41.078 --> 00:12:42.530
So off he went to Paris.

00:12:42.530 --> 00:12:44.660
And the Michelin
Guide removed one star

00:12:44.660 --> 00:12:49.170
from one of his
restaurants just because he

00:12:49.170 --> 00:12:51.331
was moving as a chef.

00:12:51.331 --> 00:12:53.080
That's the politics
of the Michelin Guide,

00:12:53.080 --> 00:12:55.310
and they do work
in mysterious ways.

00:12:55.310 --> 00:12:59.600
He got it back instantly,
which he deserved.

00:12:59.600 --> 00:13:02.870
And that was the beginning of
the Alain Ducasse adventure

00:13:02.870 --> 00:13:04.890
and venturing out worldwide.

00:13:04.890 --> 00:13:08.040
So many restaurants
in Paris, Monaco,

00:13:08.040 --> 00:13:11.000
and all over the
world, including

00:13:11.000 --> 00:13:13.710
London, of course, as well.

00:13:13.710 --> 00:13:17.720
A little bit about
Alain and going global--

00:13:17.720 --> 00:13:19.870
or as you call it, glocal--

00:13:19.870 --> 00:13:52.050
ALAIN DUCASSE: [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:13:52.050 --> 00:13:54.630
MICHEL ROUX JR: I think
this is fantastic.

00:13:54.630 --> 00:13:55.620
I love this.

00:13:55.620 --> 00:13:57.960
Glocal.

00:13:57.960 --> 00:14:00.880
It really does-- it's perfect.

00:14:00.880 --> 00:14:04.180
And I don't think it's
just for us in cooking.

00:14:04.180 --> 00:14:06.330
I think it's in any business.

00:14:06.330 --> 00:14:12.290
Wherever you go, you may be a
global brand-- in his instance,

00:14:12.290 --> 00:14:15.130
he is a global brand
in his own right--

00:14:15.130 --> 00:14:21.670
but he will use local produce,
local workforce where possible,

00:14:21.670 --> 00:14:30.110
and not forgetting he is
cooking for a local customer.

00:14:30.110 --> 00:14:32.640
So in America, he will
be cooking for Americans.

00:14:32.640 --> 00:14:34.610
In London, he's
cooking for Londoners,

00:14:34.610 --> 00:14:35.650
or for British people.

00:14:35.650 --> 00:14:37.310
In Paris, for Parisians.

00:14:37.310 --> 00:14:39.740
And that is very important.

00:14:39.740 --> 00:14:43.000
And it's the key to
success in most businesses.

00:14:43.000 --> 00:14:46.130
If he were to force or ram
down the throat-- in New York,

00:14:46.130 --> 00:14:49.864
for example-- typically French,
and have it all imported

00:14:49.864 --> 00:14:51.530
and all that, it
probably wouldn't work.

00:14:51.530 --> 00:14:53.670
Or it wouldn't be
as well-respected.

00:14:53.670 --> 00:14:58.010
And I think that is really the
key to the Alain Ducasse brand

00:14:58.010 --> 00:15:02.350
and the strength--
his glocal vision.

00:15:02.350 --> 00:15:06.200
And I think he should be really
highly commended for that.

00:15:06.200 --> 00:15:30.259
ALAIN DUCASSE: [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:15:30.259 --> 00:15:32.050
MICHEL ROUX JR: I think
what Alain has just

00:15:32.050 --> 00:15:33.633
said there is very
important, as well.

00:15:33.633 --> 00:15:38.120
I think all great chefs are
teachers-- natural teachers--

00:15:38.120 --> 00:15:41.030
and want to pass
on their knowledge.

00:15:41.030 --> 00:15:44.410
Alain has written many,
many books-- great books.

00:15:44.410 --> 00:15:46.320
And it's all part of his psyche.

00:15:46.320 --> 00:15:50.610
It's part of him being
a very generous chef.

00:15:50.610 --> 00:15:52.530
He has cooking schools, as well.

00:15:52.530 --> 00:15:54.700
It's all part of his philosophy.

00:15:54.700 --> 00:15:57.800
And my father and uncle-- the
Roux Scholarship, for example--

00:15:57.800 --> 00:16:01.070
that's been going on for 31
years helping British chefs

00:16:01.070 --> 00:16:02.370
to achieve their goals.

00:16:05.170 --> 00:16:09.570
We all too often see young
chefs who are in the limelight

00:16:09.570 --> 00:16:13.110
and trying to get the glory,
but don't think of the future.

00:16:13.110 --> 00:16:15.470
And the future is
passing on your knowledge

00:16:15.470 --> 00:16:18.360
and being generous
with your time.

00:16:18.360 --> 00:16:20.220
And I think that
is something which

00:16:20.220 --> 00:16:23.070
Alain is very generous with
his time, and very generous

00:16:23.070 --> 00:16:25.970
with his staff, as well.

00:16:25.970 --> 00:16:47.797
ALAIN DUCASSE: [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:16:47.797 --> 00:16:49.130
MICHEL ROUX JR: Yes, absolutely.

00:16:49.130 --> 00:16:52.410
Cooking is happening
all over the world.

00:16:52.410 --> 00:16:56.160
It doesn't matter where you're
from-- on what continent, what

00:16:56.160 --> 00:16:59.110
the color of your skin
is-- everybody cooks,

00:16:59.110 --> 00:17:00.850
and everybody has a heritage.

00:17:00.850 --> 00:17:03.060
And that's certainly
very important.

00:17:03.060 --> 00:17:05.260
And it's so beautiful.

00:17:05.260 --> 00:17:11.430
But cooking evolves and
moves-- moves at a steady pace,

00:17:11.430 --> 00:17:13.500
and moves with us.

00:17:13.500 --> 00:17:17.640
And it's up to us, as chefs,
to express that, as well.

00:17:17.640 --> 00:17:19.270
