00:34:35.570 --> 00:34:37.580
Television came later.

00:34:37.580 --> 00:34:40.739
So those youngsters that
come into the industry

00:34:40.739 --> 00:34:42.870
on the false pretense--
on the pretense of being

00:34:42.870 --> 00:34:45.469
the next television chef--
they normally get it wrong,

00:34:45.469 --> 00:34:47.699
and they go away
very, very, very soon.

00:34:47.699 --> 00:34:51.790
Personally, I do think
that it's a good thing.

00:34:51.790 --> 00:34:54.639
But not all programs.

00:34:54.639 --> 00:34:57.530
I don't know if you guys know
about my spat-- recent spat--

00:34:57.530 --> 00:34:58.210
with the BBC.

00:34:58.210 --> 00:34:59.210
I walked away from them.

00:34:59.210 --> 00:35:00.470
But that's another story.

00:35:00.470 --> 00:35:04.660
That's just editorial policy and
the BBC being very pig-headed.

00:35:07.285 --> 00:35:10.430
Just needed to get it
off my chest, sorry.

00:35:10.430 --> 00:35:11.700
But I will do something.

00:35:11.700 --> 00:35:13.560
I will do something
else, maybe with Google.

00:35:13.560 --> 00:35:16.120
Who knows?

00:35:16.120 --> 00:35:19.270
You do TV, or that
kind of stuff.

00:35:19.270 --> 00:35:22.050
It's interesting.

00:35:22.050 --> 00:35:25.180
But I do believe,
like Alain, that media

00:35:25.180 --> 00:35:29.000
plays a very strong
part in our industry

00:35:29.000 --> 00:35:33.630
for the stuff
coming in, but also

00:35:33.630 --> 00:35:38.260
for the public because
there is an interest.

00:35:38.260 --> 00:35:39.610
They see the food.

00:35:39.610 --> 00:35:42.040
And I see this in
England, especially,

00:35:42.040 --> 00:35:45.120
where if I take an example
of snails-- 20 years ago,

00:35:45.120 --> 00:35:47.030
you put snails on
the menu in England,

00:35:47.030 --> 00:35:48.660
and we just wouldn't sell it.

00:35:48.660 --> 00:35:49.720
It wouldn't go.

00:35:49.720 --> 00:35:52.260
Or you would occasionally
get people who would buy it,

00:35:52.260 --> 00:35:53.390
but it-- no.

00:35:53.390 --> 00:35:56.650
And if you asked the
customer, why would

00:35:56.650 --> 00:35:58.020
you not want to eat snails?

00:35:58.020 --> 00:36:00.520
The answer was, I
don't like them.

00:36:00.520 --> 00:36:02.180
Have you tried them, sir?

00:36:02.180 --> 00:36:04.740
No, I just don't like them.

00:36:04.740 --> 00:36:07.470
Now it's totally different.

00:36:07.470 --> 00:36:09.840
The British public
want to try them.

00:36:09.840 --> 00:36:11.010
They are curious.

00:36:11.010 --> 00:36:14.100
And that curiosity
has come through media

00:36:14.100 --> 00:36:18.070
and through wanting to
learn and wanting to taste.

00:36:18.070 --> 00:36:20.393
And that's been television
led and media led.

